[["Map",1,2,109,110],"blog",["Map",3,4,40,41,64,65,89,90],"post-1",{"id":3,"data":5,"body":17,"filePath":18,"digest":19,"rendered":20},{"title":6,"pubDate":7,"description":8,"author":9,"image":10,"tags":13},"My First Blog Post",["Date","2022-07-01T00:00:00.000Z"],"This is the first post of my new Astro blog.","Astro Learner",{"url":11,"alt":12},"https://docs.astro.build/assets/rose.webp","The Astro logo on a dark background with a pink glow.",[14,15,16],"astro","blogging","learning in public","# My First Blog Post\r\n\r\nPublished on: 2022-07-01\r\n\r\nWelcome to my _new blog_ about learning Astro! Here, I will share my learning journey as I build a new website.\r\n\r\n## What I've accomplished\r\n\r\n1. **Installing Astro**: First, I created a new Astro project and set up my online accounts.\r\n\r\n2. **Making Pages**: I then learned how to make pages by creating new `.astro` files and placing them in the `src/pages/` folder.\r\n\r\n3. **Making Blog Posts**: This is my first blog post! I now have Astro pages and Markdown posts!\r\n\r\n## What's next\r\n\r\nI will finish the Astro tutorial, and then keep adding more posts. Watch this space for more to come.","src/blog/post-1.md","f830f122fb6792a9",{"html":21,"metadata":22},"\u003Ch1 id=\"my-first-blog-post\">My First Blog Post\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>Published on: 2022-07-01\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Welcome to my \u003Cem>new blog\u003C/em> about learning Astro! Here, I will share my learning journey as I build a new website.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"what-ive-accomplished\">What I’ve accomplished\u003C/h2>\n\u003Col>\n\u003Cli>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Installing Astro\u003C/strong>: First, I created a new Astro project and set up my online accounts.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Making Pages\u003C/strong>: I then learned how to make pages by creating new \u003Ccode>.astro\u003C/code> files and placing them in the \u003Ccode>src/pages/\u003C/code> folder.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Making Blog Posts\u003C/strong>: This is my first blog post! I now have Astro pages and Markdown posts!\u003C/p>\n\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ol>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"whats-next\">What’s next\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>I will finish the Astro tutorial, and then keep adding more posts. Watch this space for more to come.\u003C/p>",{"headings":23,"localImagePaths":34,"remoteImagePaths":35,"frontmatter":36,"imagePaths":39},[24,27,31],{"depth":25,"slug":26,"text":6},1,"my-first-blog-post",{"depth":28,"slug":29,"text":30},2,"what-ive-accomplished","What I’ve accomplished",{"depth":28,"slug":32,"text":33},"whats-next","What’s next",[],[],{"title":6,"pubDate":7,"description":8,"author":9,"image":37,"tags":38},{"url":11,"alt":12},[14,15,16],[],"post-2",{"id":40,"data":42,"body":51,"filePath":52,"digest":53,"rendered":54},{"title":43,"pubDate":44,"description":45,"author":9,"image":46,"tags":49},"My Second Blog Post",["Date","2022-07-08T00:00:00.000Z"],"After learning some Astro, I couldn't stop!",{"url":47,"alt":48},"https://docs.astro.build/assets/arc.webp","The Astro logo on a dark background with a purple gradient arc.",[14,15,16,50],"successes","After a successful first week learning Astro, I decided to try some more. I wrote and imported a small component from memory!","src/blog/post-2.md","75acbd2fd49cfb45",{"html":55,"metadata":56},"\u003Cp>After a successful first week learning Astro, I decided to try some more. I wrote and imported a small component from memory!\u003C/p>",{"headings":57,"localImagePaths":58,"remoteImagePaths":59,"frontmatter":60,"imagePaths":63},[],[],[],{"title":43,"author":9,"description":45,"image":61,"pubDate":44,"tags":62},{"url":47,"alt":48},[14,15,16,50],[],"post-3",{"id":64,"data":66,"body":76,"filePath":77,"digest":78,"rendered":79},{"title":67,"pubDate":68,"description":69,"author":9,"image":70,"tags":73},"My Third Blog Post",["Date","2022-07-15T00:00:00.000Z"],"I had some challenges, but asking in the community really helped!",{"url":71,"alt":72},"https://docs